The paper also discusses parallelization schemes and performance models, which are related to high-performance computing, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with image classification tasks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the potential of the Intel Xeon Phi coprocessor, which is a hardware-related topic, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the empirical and theoretical evaluation of the proposed approach, which is related to the evaluation of algorithms and systems, making cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) another possible category.
